 cell damage. Its potential in treating cardiovascular diseases is also attributed to its ability to lower blood pressure and cholesterol levels, due to the presence of compounds such as flavonoids and phenolic acids.", "constituents": [], "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Polygonum forsteri are phenolic compounds, particularly emodin, rhein, and chrysophanic acid, which exhibit anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties. These compounds have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and enzymes, thereby reducing inflammation and tissue damage. Additionally, Polygonum forsteri contains flavonoids, such as quercetin and kaempferol, which possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, and terpenoids, including limonene and beta-pinene, which display antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects. The presence of these bioactive compounds in Polygonum forsteri contributes to its traditional use in the treatment of various conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and skin disorders. The pharmacological activities of Polygonum forsteri are attributed to the synergistic action of its diverse bioactive constituents, which work together to produce a range of beneficial effects.", "herb_names_common": [], "preparations": [{"name": "tincture", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 165, "total_score": 3300}, {"name": "infusion", "mentions": 19, "confidence_score": 153, "total_score": 2907}, {"name": "tea", "mentions": 17, "confidence_score": 123, "total_score": 2091}, {"name": "salve", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 104, "total_score": 2080}, {"name": "decoction", "mentions": 15, "confidence_score": 81, "total_score": 1215}, {"name": "ointment", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 21, "total_score": 105}, {"name": "infused oil", "mentions": 3, "confidence_score": 19, "total_score": 57}, {"name": "oil", "mentions": 2, "confidence_score": 8, "total_score": 16}, {"name": "essential oil", "menti